cs.MS, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a software utility for facilitating parallel parameter sweeps with computational models.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the utility supports dispatching parallel jobs for each parameter set, with support for common high-performance computing (HPC) job schedulers.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the utility involves generating parameter sets and post-processing the results.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the utility can be used with computational models that involve neural networks or evolutionary algorithms.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but possible as the utility involves minimal code changes to the model's existing configuration files using a template system.
